</paragraph>
<paragraph id="03421E604C68FF9FFED9FB6E6D1DFAA2" blockId="14.[264,1323,1164,1310]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The female specimen examined by Bezzi (
<number id="B5350C474C68FF9FFCD4FB6E6C31FB1A" box="[773,833,1164,1190]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1921.0">1921</number>
a) is designated 
<typeStatus id="DC46A0C24C68FF9FFBD2FB6E6B02FB1A" box="[1027,1138,1164,1190]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">lectotype</typeStatus>
, being the only specimen associated with the key and diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="C4FD65E34C68FF9FFCB6FB566C8DFB71" box="[871,1021,1204,1229]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pubescens">
<emphasis id="3189C2724C68FF9FFCB6FB566C8DFB71" box="[871,1021,1204,1229]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P. pubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Thus, Hesse (
<number id="B5350C474C68FF9FFB7EFB566B9CFB72" box="[1199,1260,1204,1230]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="1938.0">1938</number>
) was incorrect in subsequently designating a male specimen as 
<typeStatus id="DC46A0C24C68FF9FFC04FB3E6B4CFB4A" box="[981,1084,1244,1270]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
but his description fully characterises the species.
</paragraph>
